column10:
 I really want to like this game but i just can't .Crysis 1 so frustrated and bad . I gave it a 4/10 

 { Graphics } 

+ it is a Remastered version of course it gonna look good. The lighting and shadow is good with highly detailed environments and impressive visual effects , i love how the dev make the option " can it run crysis " in the graphics setting refer to the meme back in the day 

 { Gameplay }

- This is the aspect where Crysis 1 suffer the most, the gameplay is straight up trash and " no fun allow "

- The game let you play as an US special forces soldier with a million dollar nano armor suit, but for f*ck sake you feel just like a normal soldier , you die after 3 to 4 shoot so does your enemies , at what point does the suit make you more superior than them ,oh yeah the suit has enhanced armor mode so you can take an extra 2 bullet do you hear that you can tank up to 2 MORE BULLET BEFORE YOU DIE . The suit also provide you with invisible cloak but the stealth system is so f*ck up that it make the invisible mode useless , it drain power so much you can barely sneak through enemies, OH you want to take the enemies one by one sorry ! but the moment you pull the trigger the cloak disabled and energy turn to 0% WHAT ??? . The only thing decent about the suit is it allow you to sprint very fast and it change color depend on the mode you active 

- The AI is soooo broken , enemies probably have 100/10 eyesight since they can spot you 10km away , sometime they can even see you through invisible cloak . In short to mid range enemies accurate is insane,  they tend to spray the entire magazine on you and like i said earlier " you die after a few shoot " . The enemies movement feel very unnatural they dodge bullet like NEO in the Matrix . 

- Gunplay is clunky and dated, i don't mind if the gun have recoil well it supposed to have recoil but i do mind when the gun sake like crazy every time you shoot, don't you think an US special forces soldier with nano suit should be able to handle a bit of recoil ?

- I love the amount of freedom you have in the first 6 mission. You don't restricted to a path but the dev fail to make the map fun to explore. Oh you can go any where but the only thing you find is stupid enemies, wouldn't it be more interest if you put some thing for player to find like unique weapon , audio document to expand the lore or rescute some marine being capture instead of DOWNLOADING SOME DATA

 { Story }
- At this point the game is too bad for me to even care about the story. So basiclly you go shoot North korean and alient
- Character is not memoriable since they all f*cking die after a short time they on screen, oh man ! me and the gang gonna pull up to North korean island and blow some sh*t up can't wait to get to know more about my team oh wait ! they all DEATH 30m later

 { PC requirement }

- You gonna need a decent laptop/pc to play this game 

 { Bugs } 

- i don't notice any bug

 { Should you buy it ? } 

- Even when this game is on sales i don't think it gonna worth your money

 { Final thought }

- Crysis 1 is too overrated , maybe it is good and revolutionized back in the day but in today standard it is just a bad shooting game with weird design and wasted potential. i bought Crysis to be a badass killing machine and this game fail to deliver that
